(\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial y})^2+Sin^2(\theta)(\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial y})^2=1
[\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial  x} \frac{\partial \theta}{\partial  y}+ Sin^2(\theta)\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial  x} \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial  y}]=0
\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial x}=\psi
\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial y}=\chi
\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial x}=\frac{1}{Sin \theta}\chi
\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial y}= - \frac{1}{Sin \theta}\psi
\psi^2+\chi^2=1
\frac{\partial \psi}{\partial  y}=\frac {\partial \chi }{\partial x}
\frac{\partial}{\partial y}\frac{1}{Sin \theta}{\chi}=-\frac{\partial}{\partial x}\frac{1}{Sin \theta}{\psi}
-\frac{Cos^2 \theta}{Sin \theta}\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial y}\chi+\frac{1}{Sin\theta}\frac{\partial \chi}{\partial y}= \frac{Cos^2 \theta}{Sin \theta}\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial x}\psi+\frac{1}{Sin\theta}\frac{\partial \psi}{\partial x}
\frac{Cos^2 \theta}{Sin \theta}(\chi^2+\psi^2)=\frac{1}{Sin \theta}(\frac{\partial \psi}{\partial x}+\frac{\partial \chi}{\partial y})
